-- Meirelles Says Central Bank Trying to Shield Brazil From Excessive Inflows
-- B y   S i m o n e   M e i e r
-- 2010-11-19T14:14:37Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-11-19/meirelles-says-central-bank-trying-to-shield-brazil-from-excessive-inflows.html
Brazilian central bank President
Henrique Meirelles said policy makers are taking measures to
prevent excessive capital inflows.  Meirelles, speaking to reporters in Frankfurt, said that
central bank is strengthening “prudential rules” to assure
against excessive credit expansion.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Simone Meier in Frankfurt at 
